    "content_hash": "b4b11de83cf4ff15",
    "department": "Product \u0026 Design",
    "description": "What Makes You a Great Fit\n\nWe are a small group of creative and passionate product designers who help define, create, and design all user facing aspects of the Pebl brand and products. We partner and work closely with product and engineering teams to define the user experiences, translate the definitions into complete end experience that can be tested, delivered and iterated on. We are looking for a Lead Product Designer to join our growing Design Team.\n\nIn office collaboration is required Monday - Wednesday. You will be an individual contributor reporting to the Director of Product Design\n\n \n\nHow You'll Make an Impact:\n\n - Design and develop the end-to-end experience of the customer journey starting with them exploring on the Pebl website\n\n - Develop and maintain design standards, guidelines, and best practices across the organization\n\n - Design and deliver high-quality, user-centered design solutions that meet business objectives and user needs\n\n - Conduct user research, usability testing, and A/B testing to inform design decisions and drive product improvements\n\n - Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including product management, engineering, and marketing to ensure design solutions meet business objectives\n\n - Create and maintain design documentation, including design specifications, wireframes, and prototypes\n\n \n\nLet's Connect If You:\n\n - 5+ years of experience in UX design, with a focus on digital products and services\n\n - Portfolio that showcases expertise in user-centered design, interaction design, and visual design\n\n - Proficiency in design tools such as Sketch, Figma, Adobe XD, and InVision\n\n - Ability to present work senior stakeholders regularly\n\n - Experience with design systems, accessibility, and inclusive design principles\n\n - Certification in UX design, human-computer interaction, or a related field\n\n#LI-Hybrid\n\nOur Commitment to You\n\nAt Pebl, we’re committed to supporting our team with comprehensive rewards and benefits designed to meet diverse needs across roles and locations. Our core offerings include:\n\n - Flexible Time Off – Take the time you need to recharge.\n\n - Parental Leave – Support for growing families.\n\n - Health and Dental Insurance – Where applicable, to cover you and your loved ones.\n\n - Retirement Savings + Employee Incentive Plan – Plan for the future while sharing our success.\n\nPlease visit our career page for more information https://hellopebl.com/company/careers/.\n\nPebl is an Equal Opportunity Employer.\n\nWe power global teams and believe diverse perspectives drive innovation and impact. Employment decisions at Pebl are based on qualifications, merit, and business needs. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, sex (including pregnancy, sexual orientation, or gender identity), national origin, age, disability, genetic information, veteran status, or any other status protected by applicable law. We’re committed to fostering an inclusive culture where every teammate can thrive and do the best work of their career—anywhere in the world.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
